rComments: You need to go to lectures because she often will only mention things once and there are no slides to go back to. You get a handout with the main points of each lecture, but it's missing a lot of details. She was also super unclear on expectations, I went into the midterm with no idea what to expect. You can still get a good grade if you study tho.

Must attend lectures and note literally everything down that she says... It is almost the only time you'll hear most bits of information. Was doing exceedingly well in class until the final test. Gave us four excerpts ranging from the year 842 to 2019 and we had to date them + give 3 traits showing why we chose that date (worth 20% of the test).
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Took this class in my first year and found it to be fairly easy. The questions on the three in-class tests are nearly entirely based on events that occurred in each of the three assigned novels. The books progressively get more difficult to make sense of, though the last test (hardest book) has about 20% given to analyzing a passage so it evens out

She speaks French perfectly well. If anything, she might be a bit quiet. Not very organized, gives unclear instructions. Rambles on and goes off topic a lot. But she's a pretty generous marker (gives pity marks even if you get everything wrong).

You cannot understand her French... she is German. Aside from now being able to understand her, she was not helpful at all. Blamed the class for mistakes over and over. BTW we had about 100ish students that dropped to about 20 within 1 month or less. AVOID HER AT ALL COSTS, NOT WORTH IT I PROMISE YOU.
Run, run as fast as you can. If you can avoid taking a course with this prof, then do so. Unclear, monotone, hard marker.
Very unclear on expectations for tests/assignments, then expected very specific responses in order to receive marks. Monotone and difficult to understand during lectures as well. Definitely avoid!

I found her class to be disastrously disorganized.  This lack of thought about the material taught was reflected on the grades of a good majority of the class.  A poorly constructed syllabus, the lack of knowledge of the professor, and her defensive attitude made this course something to be avoided.  I would not recommend this professor to anyone.

I found the course to be disorganized.  She didn't lay out her expectations very clearly at all. She was approachable and helpful during office hours though. I found the class boring, and I didn't study much and didn't learn much
